<ul>
	<li/>
<p style="margin-bottom: 0in">CHAOS: Cheating is encouraged.
	Trickery is encouraged. Dirty fighting is encouraged. Unfairness is
	encouraged. Make no promises.</p>
	<li/>
<p style="margin-bottom: 0in">GOOD: Preserve life. Respect
	your enemy. Show mercy. Open your heart, even to your bitter rivals.
	Forgive others. Be charitable. Earn trust.</p>
	<li/>
<p>SMART: Keep your guard up. Pay attention, there are liars
	and cheats everywhere. Do not give trust easily.</p>
</ul>
<h1 class="western">Side Quests</h1>
<ul>
	<li/>
<p style="margin-bottom: 0in">Tubby's prescription on how to
	live forever = a sheet torn out of a book.</p>
	<ul>
		<li/>
<p style="margin-bottom: 0in">Brother Jayjay Yellowbelly, an
		old scholar at the temple, will be nervous (perception 20 to
		notice) if the party asks around the temple about the page.</p>
		<ul>
			<li/>
<p style="margin-bottom: 0in">In fact he did it to
			manipulate Tubby years ago, so he would prey upon children, and so
			cover up Jayjay's kidnap &amp; murder of his own son, which would
			cover up his infidelity.</p>
		</ul>
		<li/>
<p style="margin-bottom: 0in">The page comes from a book, a
		relic from the (now scattered) necromantic cult of Padegart swamp
		people, to the East. A goblin tribe (the three) revered this cult,
		and had lower-ranked members in it.</p>
		<ul>
			<li/>
<p style="margin-bottom: 0in">If they are interrogated, the
			Goblins say the cult is still around, and has infiltrated many
			institutions.</p>
		</ul>
	</ul>
	<li/>
<p style="margin-bottom: 0in">Emlef's parents?</p>
	<li/>
<p>PC family/friends?</p>
</ul>
<h1 class="western">Events</h1>
<h2 class="western">Event: Chase the Sun</h2>
<ul>
	<li/>
<p style="margin-bottom: 0in">Beast Tamer and Chariot Race.
	Have to build your own chariot, capture your own beasts (land only)
	and then do a full contact race in dangerous conditions</p>
	<ul>
		<li/>
<p style="margin-bottom: 0in">Steal knowledge and sabotage
		rivals during the prep phase</p>
		<li/>
<p>Battle during race, and capture trophies at checkpoints.</p>
	</ul>
</ul>
